<paragraph id="8351A36FFFBCFFC1FF41F898B6E8F8AF" blockId="5.[174,759,1803,1827]" box="[174,759,1803,1827]" pageId="5" pageNumber="210">
<treatmentCitationGroup id="A3FE8441FFBCFFC1FF41F898B6E8F8AF" box="[174,759,1803,1827]" pageId="5" pageNumber="210">
<treatmentCitation id="024F857EFFBCFFC1FF41F898B607F8AF" author="Tullgren, A." box="[174,536,1805,1827]" page="151" pageId="5" pageNumber="210" year="1910">
<taxonomicName id="44EED8ECFFBCFFC1FF41F898B607F8AF" authority="Tullgren, 1910: 151" authorityName="Tullgren" authorityPageNumber="151" authorityYear="1910" box="[174,536,1805,1827]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Meta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="merianopsis">
<emphasis id="B19A7F7DFFBCFFC1FF41F898B548F8AF" box="[174,343,1806,1827]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="210">Meta merianopsis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E77FDE9EFFBCFFC1FEB2F89BB607F8AF" author="Tullgren, A." box="[349,536,1805,1827]" pageId="5" pageNumber="210" pagination="85 - 172" refId="ref5137" refString="Tullgren, A. 1910. Araneae. In: Wissenschaftliche Ergebnisse der Schwedischen Zoologischen Expedition nach dem Kilimandjaro, dem Meru und dem Umbegenden Massaisteppen Deutsch-Ostafrikas 1905 - 1906 unter Leitung von Prof. Dr Yngve Sjostedt. Stockholm, 20 (6), 85 - 172." type="journal article" year="1910">Tullgren, 1910: 151</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
, pl. 3, f. 75, a–d (♂, 
<specimenCount id="95E868E6FFBCFFC1FD35F89DB6F6F8AE" box="[730,745,1803,1826]" pageId="5" pageNumber="210" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
).
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8351A36FFFBFFFC2FF34FF39B683FEE6" blockId="6.[166,1225,173,362]" pageId="6" pageNumber="211">
Note. The species was described based on a large series of 
<typeStatus id="5C551DCDFFBFFFC2FC4DFF39B018FF46" box="[930,1031,175,202]" pageId="6" pageNumber="211">syntypes</typeStatus>
(68 ♂, 
<specimenCount id="95E868E6FFBFFFC2FB87FF3BB064FF46" box="[1128,1147,173,202]" pageId="6" pageNumber="211" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
) from Meru and 
<collectingRegion id="412A6D8DFFBFFFC2FECEFF59B5B0FF66" box="[289,431,207,234]" country="Tanzania" name="Kilimanjaro" pageId="6" pageNumber="211">Kilimanjaro</collectingRegion>
Mountains (
<collectingCountry id="FBF9E3FFFFBFFFC2FDA8FF59B6A4FF66" box="[583,699,207,234]" name="Tanzania" pageId="6" pageNumber="211">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
). The 
<bibRefCitation id="E77FDE9EFFBFFFC2FCEFFF59B78EFF66" author="WSC" box="[768,913,207,234]" pageId="6" pageNumber="211" refId="ref5187" refString="WSC, 2017. World Spider Catalog. Natural History Museum Bern. (http: // wsc. nmbe. ch, version 18.0; accessed: 28.02.2017)." type="url" year="2017">WSC (2017)</bibRefCitation>
erroneously indicates that this species is known from females only, although Tullgren provided a clear description of the male and illustrated palp. Judging from the figures of the male palp and the species name meaning “resembling 
<taxonomicName id="44EED8ECFFBFFFC2FE41FEA6B603FEC5" box="[430,540,304,329]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Metellina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="merianae">
<emphasis id="B19A7F7DFFBFFFC2FE41FEA6B603FEC5" box="[430,540,304,329]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="211">merianae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” (
<taxonomicName id="44EED8ECFFBFFFC2FDD4FEB9B73DFEC5" box="[571,802,303,329]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Metellina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="merianae">
<emphasis id="B19A7F7DFFBFFFC2FDD4FEB9B73DFEC5" box="[571,802,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="211">Metellina merianae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was considered 
<taxonomicName id="44EED8ECFFBFFFC2FC05FEA6B038FEC5" baseAuthorityName="WSC" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[1002,1063,304,329]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Meta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B19A7F7DFFBFFFC2FC05FEA6B038FEC5" box="[1002,1063,304,329]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="211">Meta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Tullgren’s time), we transfer this species to 
<taxonomicName id="44EED8ECFFBFFFC2FDC9FED9B68AFEE5" authorityName="Chamberlin &amp; Ivie" authorityYear="1941" box="[550,661,335,361]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Metellina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B19A7F7DFFBFFFC2FDC9FED9B68AFEE5" box="[550,661,335,361]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="211">Metellina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
